# DVC Configuration for California Housing MLOps Pipeline

# Data versioning configuration
# This file tracks the California Housing dataset and ensures reproducible data pipeline

# Dataset information
# Source: scikit-learn California Housing dataset
# Features: 8 numerical features (MedInc, HouseAge, AveRooms, AveBedrms, Population, AveOccup, Latitude, Longitude)
# Target: Median house value (in hundreds of thousands)
# Samples: ~20,640 samples

# To initialize DVC in this project:
# 1. Run: dvc init
# 2. Track the dataset: dvc add data/california_housing.csv
# 3. Commit changes: git add data/california_housing.csv.dvc .dvc/config
# 4. Add remote storage (optional): dvc remote add -d myremote <storage-url>
# 5. Push data (optional): dvc push

# Example remote configurations:

# Local remote (for development)
# dvc remote add -d local /path/to/local/storage

# AWS S3 remote
# dvc remote add -d s3remote s3://my-bucket/dvc-storage
# dvc remote modify s3remote profile myprofile

# Google Cloud Storage remote
# dvc remote add -d gcsremote gs://my-bucket/dvc-storage
# dvc remote modify gcsremote project my-project-id

# Azure Blob Storage remote
# dvc remote add -d azureremote azure://my-container/dvc-storage
# dvc remote modify azureremote connection_string "..."

# Note: We're versioning the California Housing dataset directly to
# demonstrate best practices for dataset versioning.
# This way, the dataset is tracked and can be shared, while keeping
# the repository size manageable by using DVC.
